The '''Independence Day of Mongolia''' ({{lang-mn|Монгол Улсын тусгаар тогтнол}}) is the main state holiday in [[Mongolia]]. This date is celebrated annually on 29 December. It marks Mongolia's independence from [[China]] in 1921. It has been celebrated annually in [[Mongolia]] since 2011. Independence Day is also the term used for Constitution Day on November 26.

== Background ==
In May 1911, the [[Manchuria|Manchurian]] [[Qing dynasty]] was overthrown and [[Mongolia]] under [[Bogd Khan]] [[Mongolian Revolution of 1911|declared its independence]] on December 29, 1911.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://anydayguide.com/calendar/2775|title=National Independence Day in Mongolia / December 29, 2017|last=AnydayGuide|work=AnydayGuide|access-date=2017-09-24|language=en-GB}}</ref><ref>[https://ruspekh.ru/events/item/den-nezavisimosti-mongolii День Независимости Монголии]</ref> The newly established [[Republic of Mongolia]] lasted for 8 years until it was invaded by the [[Republic of China]] in 1919 and by [[Russia]] in early 1921.<ref>[http://asiarussia.ru/news/5547/ Сегодня в Монголии годовщина национальной революции - День независимости!]</ref><ref>[https://anydaylife.com/calendar/2775 День независимости Монголии]</ref>

